posts.author: TateDemarcus
posts.title: Troll the Feds

posts.raw_content:
Legacy media didn’t just get the story wrong about this 5 year old in Minneapolis.
What they did was, and always is, something more nefarious. They blatantly manipulate reality to create outrage and animosity for profit.

Every outlet led with “5-year-old detained by ICE” because outrage is the product. The truth is the obstacle.

The father—the actual target of the enforcement action—was buried deep in the articles because context ruins the emotional payload. That is not journalism. That is manipulative framing designed to hijack your reaction before your brain ever sees the facts.

Worse, when there were conflicting accounts, the media made no visible effort to investigate which one was true. No mention of asking for body-cam footage. No mention of checking nearby surveillance cameras. No mention of asking ICE why the encounter began, whether the father was suspected of other violations, or whether standard child-custody protocols were followed. No disclosure of what was asked, what was refused, or what couldn’t be verified.

That omission is not accidental. It’s dereliction.

And then came the lie dressed up as reporting: “ICE used the child as bait.”
No evidence. No verification. No common-sense context. Just an inflammatory accusation dropped into print because it sounds good and spreads fast.

They claimed that "a person of the same household said they would care for the boy but was refused." They didn’t bother explaining that ICE cannot legally hand a child to an unverified adult, no matter how loudly that adult claims to be family. They didn’t bother explaining that trying to locate a parent is standard custodial procedure, not entrapment. And they didn’t bother explaining that if ICE hadn’t tried to find the mother, the headline would’ve been “ICE separates families without even checking if mom was home.”

This is why people hate legacy media.
Not because they ask hard questions—but because they don’t.
Not because they challenge narratives as they should- but because they intentionally create them.
Not because they make mistakes—but because they never show their work, because there is nothing to show.

What we’re watching isn’t bias. It’s propaganda economics: emotional manipulation for clicks, moral signaling for credibility within their bubble, and zero accountability for accuracy.

The press used to investigate.
Now it agitates.
It used to verify.
Now it frames.
It used to inform.
Now it activates outrage.

And they take zero responsibility for why they are seen as a joke.

They didn't lose public trust because some omnipresent phantom villain perpetrated this extraordinary campaign to damage their credibility. The trust eroded  because of shit like this. Exactly shit like this. They are fucking scum who deserve every bit of hate they receive and more.
